adviseScripts.text: Counselor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: If you and I went on a date in the Ark,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: what would you want to do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Take a walk while picking up bottle caps.
Watch a movie.
Oooh, such a unique date idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: If it were together with you, I suppose it'd be fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Then we'd have to go to a movie theater...
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I'm not a fan of enclosed spaces.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have a pleasurable time speaking with one another.
Counselor!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What would you do if you were trapped in an endless maze?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I'd ask you to come save me.
I'd pick a spot and not move from there.
You would?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Plucking you out of a maze would be easy as pie for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I'd get you out of there, no problem.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What would you do if no one went looking for you though?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: ... I guess I could come save you if you wanted.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I talk more about mazes.
Quency is nowhere to be seen.
Boo! Hehe, did I scare you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Pretend to be scared.
Sorry, you didn't get me.
Oh jeez, are you okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I didn't think you'd scare that easily.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You're a bit of a scaredy-cat, aren't you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You can't fool me! I saw you jump.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You were scared.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have a pleasant session.
Counselor, if I ever leave the rehabilitation center,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: what's the first thing you'd want to do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I'd buy you some tofu.
I'd buy you some light croquettes.
Tofu?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Blech, I hate tofu.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Something else, please.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That'd be awesome!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: We can eat it together.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have a pleasant session.
I wonder what it feels like to be free?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Freedom is a concept that I can't even fully comprehend.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Aren't you free right now?
If you were free, you could come see me whenever you wanted.
That's true, but I'm not completely free.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I wonder if it's any different from what I have now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Actually, I can do that now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: For example, I'm going to come see you again tomorrow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I speak with Quency about freedom.
Counselor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Help me come up with a nickname.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I need to use an alias when I'm doing business.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: The Escape Artist.
Why not use your name? Quency is a fine name.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: It's okay, but nothing special. Got anything else?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Hehe. Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: All right, I'll just use my real name then.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Quency coming up with nicknames.
I'm thinking of creating a new escape route.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What kind should I make?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: One that leads to my heart.
Don't you think you already have enough escape routes as is?
Haha, I don't want to brag,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: but I think I can get there easily enough already.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You never know when they'll find one of them and block it off. The more routes you have, the better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Come on, this stuff is prison breaking 101!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I contemplate new potential escape routes.
Counselor,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: feel like bartering?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Got any good items on you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: A limited-edition Ark Ranger figurine.
An adult magazine.
Hmm, I'm not sure if that'd be a big hit in the rehabilitation center.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Then again, maybe I'll take it just in case.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: *Gasp* Really? I'll take it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That'll sell like hot cakes in the rehabilitation center.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Wait a minute... why do you even have that in the first place?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I spend time exchanging items with Quency.
I have to ask.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Do you prefer Guilty, or Sin?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: None of them can beat you.
Let me think...
Hey, I was asking about those two, not me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, very smooth, Counselor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You're number one in my book as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Do you really need to think that hard about it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I'm going to tell Guilty and Sin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That is, unless you give me some bottle caps, then perhaps I'll be able to keep this between us.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
Counseling me must be a real challenge for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Especially since I disappear pretty much on a daily basis.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: If I'm being honest, it can be trying.
It's not hard at all.
Is it really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... I didn't expect you to be so candid.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, that's good then!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I don't know if I've ever told you, but I really do enjoy our sessions together.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
I'm curious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What's the perfect woman, in your mind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Someone bright and bubbly, like you.
My lips are sealed.
Do you really mean it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I asked that question because I was hoping that'd be your answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: As for me, you're very much my type as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Aw, c'mon! That only makes me more curious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Can't you at least give me a hint? Just one word.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Quency talking about what we value in a partner.
Just because I've always got a smile on my face,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: people think they can take advantage of me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Start walking around looking scary.
In the end, the person who is smiling is the real winner.
I've considered that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: But I think it'd end up negatively affecting my mood.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You're right,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: but I just get so peeved sometimes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Then again, whoever is smiling in the end is the true victor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
Hm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What's your stance on hardened criminals?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I don't have an opinion.
They scare me.
You don't?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You don't seem to have many preconceptions about other people.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That's a relief. I thought you might be afraid of them right from the jump.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: They do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: So... do you find me scary as well?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I talk more about hardened criminals.
I've been wondering.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: What was your first impression of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You seemed like you'd pose quite the challenge.
I thought you were pretty.
A challenge? How so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You mean it wouldn't be easy to win me over?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I thought you were pretty good-looking too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I talk about first impressions with Quency.
Apparently mint chocolate is all the rage in the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Have you tried it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Heck no. Sounds like it'd taste like toothpaste.
I've been trying to get my hands on some, but it's always sold out.
I don't understand it myself either.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Since it's popular, I thought about selling it at the rehabilitation center, but I'm not sure if it'll be a big seller.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Yikes, is it really that bad?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Certainly doesn't sound appetizing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Should I try selling it at the rehabilitation center?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I converse a little more about supply and demand.
Hey, Counselor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Do you have a girlfriend?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I just thought it would be good to know.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I don't.
I do.
Phew, that's a relief!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I thought you did.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Liar!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: ... You're not lying to me, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
Counselor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Counselor! Counselor? Couuunnseellooorrrr!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: WHAT?!
Quency! Quency? Quuiinncccyyyy!
I was just trying to get your attention.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You don't have to get nasty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Looks like someone got up on the wrong side of the bed this morning.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, very funny.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That's why I like you, Counselor. You've got a sense of humor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
I haven't been able to get a wink of sleep for the past few days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Beats me as to why. It's not like anything has been weighing on my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: We can try sleeping alongside each other.
Try counting sheep.
You're not pulling my leg, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'll come to your room later tonight.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Already tried it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: One sheep... Two sheep...
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Ugh! So boring.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I talk a little more about sleep.
Counselor,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: do you have any nicknames?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: If you do, I'll call you that once I leave the rehabilitation center.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Baby.
{AccountData.NickName}.
Baby? Okay!
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: That's what I'll call you once I'm out of here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: {AccountData.NickName}?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Nice! It feels like we've gotten closer to each other.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I discuss more nicknames with Quency.
If the day comes when you start living up on the surface,
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: what will become of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You'd be in a rehabilitation center up on the surface.
You'd be right there with me, roaming freely up on the surface.
*Gasp* You're not serious, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: If that's a joke, it's not funny.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: I wonder what it would feel like living up on the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Whatever it would be like, I hope I get to experience it soon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Quency

adviseScripts.text: Quency and I have another pleasant session.
